INSERT INTO Questions (question, answer) VALUES
('Can you share about a professor or class that had a big impact on students?', 'Professors in introductory Engineering and Computational Sciences courses often have a big impact on students. They explain concepts clearly and encourage critical thinking and curiosity.'),
('What’s advising like in Engineering and Computational Sciences?', 'Advising is very simple and easy. Everything is pretty straight forwards and its pretty easy to get in contact with you advisors.'),
('Are faculty and advisors accessible to students outside of class?', 'Most professors and advisors are approachable and responsive, regularly meeting with students during office hours or over email.'),
('Are Engineering and Computational Sciences courses more hands-on or lecture-based for students?', 'Many Engineering and Computational Sciences courses are hands-on. Students regularly code and build projects, especially in advanced classes. Even theory-heavy courses tend to include practical components.'),
('Are there capstone or senior design projects for students?', 'Yes. Engineering and Computational Sciences seniors complete a semester-long capstone. Faculty propose project ideas, and students select one to develop and present.'),
('Do Engineering and Computational Sciences professors bring in industry experience or current tech trends for students?', 'Yes. Many professors have industry backgrounds and incorporate real-world examples and emerging technologies into their teaching.'),
('Are there honors options or special tracks for high-achieving students?', 'Yes, there’s an Honors Program for students seeking deeper academic challenges. Independent research and advanced electives are also available.'),
('What types of internships or co-ops do Engineering and Computational Sciences students typically pursue?', 'Engineering and Computational Sciences students intern at software companies, engineering firms, research labs, local startups, and major organizations like Raytheon and Microsoft.'),
('How does Merrimack help students with resumes and interviews?', 'The O’Brien Center provides personalized resume reviews, mock interviews, and career fairs. Faculty also support students with feedback and opportunity recommendations.'),
('What’s the research process like for students interested in publishing?', 'Students can join ongoing faculty research or start independent projects. Those who contribute meaningfully often co-author publications.'),
('How does the O’Brien Center specifically support Engineering and Computational Sciences students?', 'The center hosts tech-focused career events, helps students find internships, and supports portfolio development and job preparation.'),
('Have Engineering and Computational Sciences students gone on to work at major companies or graduate schools?', 'Yes. Graduates have gone on to organizations like Microsoft and MITRE, or continued their education at schools such as Northeastern and UMass Amherst.'),
('How big are Engineering and Computational Sciences classes for students?', 'Engineering and Computational Sciences classes are typically small — around 15–25 students — allowing for more direct support and interaction with faculty.'),
('Are tutoring or academic support services available for Engineering and Computational Sciences students?', 'Yes. Tutoring is available through the Math Center and Peer Tutoring, especially for challenging courses like Data Structures and Circuits.'),
('Are Engineering and Computational Sciences labs accessible to students outside of class hours?', 'Yes. Most labs and makerspaces remain open in the evenings and on weekends, and students can access them with their Mack Cards.'),
('Do Engineering and Computational Sciences students collaborate across majors like CS and Engineering?', 'Yes. Collaboration between CS and Engineering students is common, especially in research and clubs that combine coding and hardware.'),
('What Engineering and Computational Sciences-related clubs are available to students?', 'Clubs include SWE, Robotics, NSBE, Let’s Innovate, the Computer Club, and others focused on tech and engineering interests.'),
('How do Engineering and Computational Sciences students balance club involvement with coursework?', 'Most clubs meet weekly and are considerate of academic demands, helping students manage both involvement and schoolwork effectively.'),
('Are there hackathons or coding competitions for students?', 'Yes. Merrimack hosts some events, and students also attend hackathons at nearby institutions for hands-on experience and networking.'),
('What leadership opportunities are available to Engineering and Computational Sciences students?', 'Students can take on leadership roles in clubs, guide team projects, or serve as peer mentors and tutors.'),
('Do Engineering and Computational Sciences students ever collaborate with students in other schools, like Business or Health Sciences?', 'Yes. Interdisciplinary collaboration happens through innovation challenges, joint classes, and service projects across schools.'),
('What’s the process like for students who start as Undecided Engineering?', 'Undecided Engineering students take general courses that apply across majors. Advisors help them explore interests before choosing a specific path.'),
('What are Engineering and Computational Sciences-specific facilities like for students?', 'Engineering and Computational Sciences facilities include modern labs, a robotics lab, and a makerspace equipped with 3D printers and other tools.'),
('How do Engineering and Computational Sciences students get around campus?', 'Most Engineering and Computational Sciences students walk or use the campus shuttle to travel between buildings.'),
('How often do Engineering and Computational Sciences students have classes across different parts of campus?', 'Most Engineering and Computational Sciences classes are held on the east side, while general education classes are typically located on the main campus.'),
('Is there housing available nearby for Engineering and Computational Sciences students?', 'Yes. Housing is available on campus for all years, and off-campus apartments are located nearby for upperclassmen.'),
('What dining options are available to Engineering and Computational Sciences students?', 'Engineering and Computational Sciences students can eat at a smaller dining location on the Engineering and Computational Sciences side or at a food truck during warmer months, both accepting meal swipes.'),
('Where do Engineering and Computational Sciences students typically study on campus?', 'Popular study spots include the second-floor lounge in the Engineering and Computational Sciences building, which is conveniently close to faculty offices.'),
('Do Engineering and Computational Sciences students prefer group study or independent study?', 'It varies. Many students study in groups for projects, while others prefer studying independently.'),
('What programming languages do Engineering and Computational Sciences students learn?', 'Students typically learn Java, Python, SQL, and sometimes JavaScript or C/C++, depending on the electives taken.'),
('What software or platforms do Engineering and Computational Sciences courses use?', 'Courses use tools like VSCode, GitHub, MATLAB, and more. Most instructors allow students to use any IDE as long as the work is completed correctly.'),
('Are Engineering and Computational Sciences students encouraged to contribute to open-source or personal projects?', 'Yes. Students are encouraged to build GitHub portfolios and some contribute to the college’s open-source utilities.'),
('What is the Engineering and Computational Sciences community like for students?', 'The Engineering and Computational Sciences community is tight-knit and supportive. Students help one another, and faculty are genuinely invested in student success.'),
('How do international or out-of-state students adapt culturally?', 'There are orientation programs, and the campus community is generally welcoming and eager to learn about different cultures and experiences.'),
('Are there programs to support students from underrepresented backgrounds?', 'Yes. Programs like Compass and mentoring initiatives through academic departments and the O’Brien Center support underrepresented students.'),
('Are there service trips, study abroad, or Engineering and Computational Sciences-related travel opportunities for students?', 'Yes. Students can study abroad during the summer or semester, and some Engineering and Computational Sciences students participate in engineering service trips through the SEND Program.'),
('What is the SEND Program for students?', 'The SEND Program offers service trips during breaks where students volunteer in U.S. and international communities, focusing on social justice and personal growth.'),
('Are summer research opportunities available for Engineering and Computational Sciences students?', 'Yes. Students can work with faculty on research over the summer, sometimes with stipends.'),
('How does tuition payment work for students?', 'Tuition is managed through the Bursar’s Office, and students can set up payment plans through the college portal.'),
('Where can students find information on scholarships or financial aid?', 'Students can contact the Financial Aid Office or visit the Merrimack website under Scholarships & Aid.'),
('How do students make a deposit?', 'Deposits are made through the Admissions Portal. The Admissions Office on the main campus is available to assist if needed.'),
('What is the Warriors at Work program for Engineering and Computational Sciences students?', 'Warriors at Work is a career development initiative from the O’Brien Center. Students can apply and learn more through their website or staff.'),
('What do students wish they knew before starting at Merrimack?', 'Many students say they wish they had reached out to professors sooner — faculty are approachable and eager to help.'),
('What’s the hardest part for students adjusting to Merrimack?', 'Balancing coursework and managing time is often a challenge at first, but support systems are in place to help.'),
('Why do students choose Merrimack over other schools?', 'Students often cite small class sizes, early research opportunities, and a strong support system as key reasons.'),
('What are students’ favorite parts about Merrimack?', 'The strong sense of community. Students appreciate being recognized and having close connections with professors and peers.');


